tafsir[4]{c,v,t}:
  28,62,"On the day their Lord will call them saying: “Where are My partners you used to worship besides Me and claim they are My partners?”"
  28,65,"On the day their Lord will call them saying: “What answer did you give My Messengers I sent to you?”"
  28,69,"And your Lord knows what their chests hide and make apparent. Nothing of this is hidden from Him and He shall reward them for it."
  28,70,"And He is Allah besides whom there is no true deity. For Him alone is praise in this world and for Him is praise in the afterlife. For Him is the decree which is implemented and which nothing can repel. And to Him alone you will be returned on the day of judgment for reckoning and recompense."